## 4. Tax Benefits (The Hidden Winner)

In Malaysia, the tax treatment of these two options is very different.

With a dedicated machinery loan (structured as Hire Purchase), you are considered the owner of the asset for tax purposes from day one. This means:
*   **Capital Allowance:** You can claim Initial Allowance (IA) and Annual Allowance (AA) to reduce your taxable income.
*   **Interest Deduction:** The interest portion of your monthly installment is a deductible business expense.

With a general business loan, you only get to deduct the interest. You don't get the same direct link to the asset's depreciation benefits unless you structure the purchase carefully.

